confirmPeriodBlocks.description: Challenge period. (Number of ETHEREUM blocks until a node is confirmed, even for L3s).

wasmModuleRoot.description: Root hash of the WASM module used for execution, like a fingerprint of the L2 logic. Can be associated with ArbOS versions.

entries.name: KintoAppRegistry
entries.description: Central system contract defining addresses that are allowed to be called by EOAs. The modified Kinto node reads this configuration and drops all other transactions from EOAs (enforced by a modified state transition function). As a result, users can only transact using a canonical smart wallet.

getSystemContracts.description: Target contracts that are exempt from the STF-enforced rule that EOAs cannot make transactions. Must include ArbRetryableTx `0x000000000000000000000000000000000000006E`, EntryPoint `0x2843C269D2a64eCfA63548E8B3Fc0FD23B7F70cb`, ArbSys `0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000064`.

entries.name: AccessManager
entries.description: OpenZeppelin AccessManager contract: Serves as a proxy contract defining the roles, permissions and delays to call functions in target contracts.

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: manage addresses that are callable by EOAs and other white-/blacklists that are enforced globally on the Kinto L2.
update the central KintoWallet implementation of all users on Kinto L2 and approve specific wallets for recovery via the turnkey recoverer.
manage the KYC status of any user (sanction status and KYC metadata) and mint/burn KintoID NFTs.
permissioned to call `confirmSanction()`, which makes a temporary sanction by a KYC_PROVIDER permanent and does not grant an exit window to the affected wallet.
transfer KYC NFTs to a different address.

entries.name: KintoID
entries.description: Manages Kinto's KYC system: The KYC_PROVIDER roles responsible for managing the KYC status and KYC metadata of user wallets. Each KintoWallet checks the KYC status of its user in this contract as part of the signature check.

pendingSanctions.description: addresses sanctioned by any KYC_PROVIDER role.

removedSanctions.description: addresses unsanctioned manually by any KYC_PROVIDER role. Mind that sanctions also expire if not confirmed (and those do not emit).

confirmedSanctions.description: addresses confirmed sanctioned by the GOVERNANCE_ROLE.
